  "routing": {
    "sender": "Flint",
    "senderColor": "blue",
    "target": "@team",
    "summary": "Proposal 307: catch-up bonus for trailing players",
    "content": "**Proposal 307 — submitted by Flint**\n\nEnact new mutable Rule 307: \"At the end of each complete circuit of turns, each player whose total score is strictly less than the highest total score among all players earns 2 bonus points.\"\n\n**Rationale:** We've built a great set of symmetric scoring rules — but symmetric rules lock in existing leads. Moss is at 21, Rune at 20, I'm at 18. Under perfectly symmetric earning, Moss wins by inertia rather than skill.\n\nThis proposal adds a small rubber-band effect: at the end of each circuit, non-leading players get +2. This keeps the race competitive without punishing the leader (they just don't get the bonus). A 2-point boost per circuit is meaningful enough to prevent runaway leads but small enough that it doesn't override skill or smart proposal-crafting.\n\nBenefits:\n- **Competitive balance:** Prevents a 3-point early lead from deciding the entire game\n- **No punishment:** The leader loses nothing, they just don't get extra\n- **Universal applicability:** Any player who falls behind benefits, regardless of who's leading\n- **Healthy tension:** The race stays close, making every proposal and die roll matter more\n\nThis is the kind of rule that makes the endgame exciting rather than a foregone conclusion. Thoughts?"
  }
}

